QR Code Generator 
Description:
This Python script allows users to generate a QR code from any text or URL input using the qrcode library. The QR code is saved as an image file (.png), which can be scanned by any QR scanner.
How It Works:
User enters the text or URL to encode.
The qrcode library converts the input into a matrix.
A PNG image of the QR code is generated and saved.
You can optionally open the image or customize it (size, colors).
